main event: An unidentified orbiting object was sighted under 10 degrees elevation on March 4, 1961.
interesting points: The observation was made via ground-radar.,The object was described as not being definitively identified.,There is a possibility that the object was a satellite, but its direction was not consistent with known satellite orbits.,The observational data were considered too general to draw a valid conclusion.,The sighting was recorded by military sources.
